genresAdvancedInfo.name: danzon
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A traditional Cuban music genre that originated in the late 19th century. Danzon is characterized by a slow, elegant tempo and features orchestral instruments such as violins, flutes, and trumpets. The genre has roots in African and European music and dance traditions and is often associated with ballroom dancing. Danzon has influenced other Latin American music genres such as salsa and mambo.
